%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20new%20metric%20bosses%20are%20tracking%3A%20How%20often%20you%20use%20AI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20illustration%20of%20surveillance%20cameras%20watching%20a%20laptop%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689cfe5ecfc04e97619b605f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWorker-tracking%20software%20providers%20say%20they've%20seen%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20demand.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECompanies%20want%20to%20maximize%20their%20AI%20investments%20and%20ensure%20workers%20aren't%20using%20unsanctioned%20tools.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENot%20using%20approved%20AI%20programs%20at%20work%20could%20negatively%20affect%20your%20career%2C%20say%20workplace%20experts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20slackers%2C%20beware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20companies%20are%20now%20tracking%20how%20often%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgithub-ceo-thomas-dohmke-microsoft-memo-tracking-ai-use-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployees%20use%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20tools%20such%20as%20ChatGPT%2C%20a%20move%20aimed%20at%20maximizing%20their%20investments%20in%20the%20trendy%20tech.%20Like%20it%20or%20not%2C%20workplace%20experts%20say%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethis%20means%20that%20staffers%20who%20don't%20hop%20aboard%20the%20AI%20train%20risk%20getting%20a%20poor%20performance%20review%20or%20worse%20%E2%80%94%20a%20pink%20slip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20understand%20that%20this%20is%20where%20the%20world%20is%20going%20and%20spend%20the%20time%20to%20upskill%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20David%20Martin%2C%20head%20of%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group's%20global%20people%20and%20organization%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-google-engineers-coding-productive-sundar-pichai-alphabet-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etracking%20the%20increase%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20hours%20of%20productivity%20created%20per%20week%20from%20its%20engineers'%20use%20of%20AI-powered%20tools%2C%20as%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported.%20On%20a%20podcast%20in%20June%2C%20the%20company's%20CEO%2C%20Sundar%20Pichai%2C%20said%20it%20had%20so%20far%20seen%20an%20estimated%2010%25%20boost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Microsoft%20has%20been%20measuring%20its%20employees'%20use%20of%20AI%20tools%20across%20various%20functions%2C%20a%20company%20spokesman%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELove%20Business%20Insider%3F%20Log%20in%20to%20Google%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fpreferences%2Fsource%3Fq%3Dbusinessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Eand%20make%20us%20a%20preferred%20source%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20giants%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Earen't%20alone.%20Three%20providers%20of%20worker-tracking%20software%2C%20which%20say%20they%20each%20serve%20thousands%20of%20corporate%20clients%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they've%20seen%20a%20sharp%20rise%20in%20demand%20for%20the%20ability%20to%20monitor%20their%20employees'%20AI%20usage%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorklytics%20lets%20employers%20track%20how%20much%20time%20teams%20of%20workers%20spend%20engaging%20with%20corporate%20AI%20tools%2C%20while%20ActivTrak%20and%20Hubstaff%20enable%20such%20monitoring%20at%20both%20the%20team%20and%20individual%20levels.%20All%20three%20can%20identify%20which%20company-approved%20AI%20tools%20workers%20are%20using%2C%20and%20the%20latter%20two%20can%20also%20flag%20the%20use%20of%20unapproved%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20have%20long%20paid%20attention%20to%20what%20workers%20do%20on%20their%20company-provided%20computers%2C%20and%20now%20AI%20oversight%20is%20part%20of%20the%20mix.%20However%2C%20employers%20typically%20don't%20go%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20make%20such%20surveillance%20apparent%2C%20said%20Tracy%20Brower%2C%20a%20Ph.d%20sociologist%20in%20Michigan%20who%20researches%20organizational%20behavior.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20workers%20tend%20to%20miss%20internal%20messages%20about%20monitoring%2C%20and%20even%20if%20they%20do%20notice%2C%20they%20often%20forget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20the%20terms%20and%20conditions%20of%20apps.%20Most%20people%20just%20click%20accept%2C%26quot%3B%20Brower%20said.%20%26quot%3BEmployees%20should%20anticipate%20their%20work%20is%20being%20tracked%20and%20they%20should%20anticipate%20a%20level%20of%20accountability%20from%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a08adea-a940-4997-83b4-c66171a2b79e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpotting%20savvy%20users%2C%20slackers%2C%20and%20saboteurs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20keeping%20tabs%20on%20workers'%20AI%20activities%20for%20multiple%20reasons%2C%20the%20software-tracking%20providers%20said.%20Some%20want%20to%20understand%20if%20and%20how%20the%20technology%20can%20benefit%20their%20bottom%20lines.%20Others%20already%20confident%20in%20AI's%20value%20are%20looking%20to%20identify%20the%20savviest%20users%2C%20best%20practices%2C%20and%20to%20compare%20results%20within%20different%20teams%20or%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20adoption%20is%20an%20existential%20challenge%20for%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Philip%20Arkcoll%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Worklytics.%20%26quot%3BIf%20all%20my%20competitors%20are%20getting%20really%20good%20at%20using%20AI%20and%20I'm%20not%2C%20that%20could%20be%20a%20serious%20challenge%20to%20the%20viability%20of%20my%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%20for%20workers%2C%20employers%20also%20want%20to%20identify%20who%20within%20their%20workforces%20aren't%20playing%20ball.%20Common%20reasons%20workers%20don't%20want%20to%20use%20AI%20include%20fear%20that%20the%20technology%20could%20make%20their%20jobs%20obsolete%20and%20concerns%20that%20the%20tools%20sometimes%20deliver%20inaccurate%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20appear%20to%20have%20good%20reason%20to%20worry%20about%20whether%20workers%20are%20using%20AI%20tools.%20Although%20more%20than%20three-quarters%20of%20leaders%20and%20managers%20say%20they%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bcg.com%2Fcapabilities%2Fartificial-intelligence%2Fgenerative-ai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenerative%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20several%20times%20a%20week%2C%20regular%20use%20among%20frontline%20employees%20has%20stalled%20at%2051%25%2C%20according%20to%20survey%20data%20from%20a%20June%20BCG%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20incentive%20for%20employers%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20what%20workers%20are%20or%20aren't%20doing%20with%20AI%20tools%20is%20to%20determine%20if%20any%20are%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-updated-terms-to-use-customer-data-to-train-ai-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunauthorized%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Such%20behavior%20could%20expose%20company%20secrets%20or%20customer%20information%2C%20potentially%20violating%20federal%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a7da456-9695-4441-8797-c87bf636fd90%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompanies'%20AI%20costs%20add%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tracking%20trend%20is%20unfolding%20at%20a%20time%20when%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecompanies%20in%20a%20range%20of%20industries%20are%20touting%20AI%20adoption%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-ai-uses-5-tools-employees-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoldman%20Sachs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpharmaceutical-companies-embrace-ai-in-drug-discovery-efforts-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshopify-ceo-tobi-lutke-employees-prove-ai-job-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShopify%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccenture-ai-reinvention-services-earnings-ceo-julie-sweet-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccenture%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20say%20the%20technology%20is%20helping%20to%20boost%20productivity%2C%20which%20could%20help%20to%20reduce%20their%20labor%20costs%20or%20increase%20output.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGathering%20insights%20into%20employees'%20usage%20of%20AI%20tools%20%E2%80%94%20or%20lack%20thereof%20%E2%80%94%20is%20important%20given%20the%20cost%20of%20licensing%2C%20training%20staff%20on%20proper%20use%2C%20and%20integrating%20the%20technology%20effectively%20into%20daily%20workflows.%20Though%20AI%20spending%20varies%20greatly%20by%20company%20size%2C%20the%20average%20total%20doubled%20in%202024%20from%20the%20year%20prior%20to%20%2410.3%20million%2C%20estimates%20management-consulting%20firm%20Bain%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20who%20don't%20want%20to%20use%20AI%20on%20the%20job%20but%20are%20expected%20to%20should%20raise%20their%20discomfort%20to%20their%20manager%2C%20said%20Henna%20Pryor%2C%20a%20workplace-performance%20strategist%20in%20the%20Philadelphia%20area.%20She%20recommends%20trying%20to%20get%20a%20better%20understanding%20of%20why%20your%20employer%20is%20pushing%20the%20technology%20before%20writing%20it%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPerhaps%20that%20clarity%20will%20give%20you%20the%20buy-in%20that%20you%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20ask%20just%20how%20essential%20it%20is%20for%20you%20specifically%20to%20be%20using%20AI%20and%20to%20what%20extent%2C%20added%20Pryor.%20Note%20that%20Microsoft's%20leaders%20are%20considering%20adding%20an%20AI-usage%20metric%20to%20its%20employee%20performance-%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-plans-potential-rethink-performance-reviews-pivot-satya-nadella-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereview%20process%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20lack%20of%20use%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20ding%20on%20your%20career%2C%20that%20is%20important%20to%20know%20and%20discuss%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BUnspoken%20expectations%20are%20just%20premeditated%20resentment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboss-track-ai-use-career-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755251162000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689cfe5ecfc04e97619b605f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboss-track-ai-use-career-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20companies%20have%20begun%20tracking%20how%20often%20employees%20use%20approved%20AI%20tools%20and%20which%20ones%20they're%20using.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sneedleman%40businessinsider.com%20(Sarah%20E.%20Needleman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboss-track-ai-use-career-2025-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fatigue%2C%20flashbacks%2C%20and%20crying%20on%20commutes%3A%205%20workers%20describe%20what%20'quiet%20cracking'%20looks%20like%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20sad%20cracked%20egg%20is%20pictured.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689e0ef1a17a8c5b4052e0d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BQuiet%20cracking%26quot%3B%20describes%20workers%20who%20feel%20unhappy%20in%20their%20job%20but%20cannot%20leave.%20Four%20workers%20described%20their%20experiences%20with%20it.%3Cp%3EVictoria%20Kotlyarchuk%20%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BQuiet%20cracking%26quot%3B%20describes%20unhappy%20or%20disengaged%20workers%20who%20stay%20at%20a%20company%20because%20they%20feel%20unable%20to%20switch%20jobs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPeople%20who%20say%20they've%20experienced%20%26quot%3Bquiet%20cracking%26quot%3B%20told%20Business%20Insider%20what%20it%20felt%20like%20and%20how%20they%20navigated%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20go%20in%20every%20day%20and%20try%20really%20hard%20not%20to%20break%20by%20lunchtime%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20worker%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20would%20hyperfixate%20on%20bad%20memories.%20Masiel%20would%20snack.%20Sara%20would%20cry%20on%20her%20way%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-cracking-warning-signs-work-employees-for-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EQuiet%20cracking%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20describes%20the%20silent%20struggle%20of%20feeling%20dissatisfied%20at%20work%20and%20unable%20to%20leave.%20Frank%20Giampietro%2C%20EY's%20chief%20well-being%20officer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20these%20employees%20%26quot%3Bfeel%20stuck%20where%20they%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnhappy%20workers%20can%20stay%20because%20they%20need%20the%20paycheck%20or%20because%20they%20worry%20that%20another%20job%20would%20be%20more%20of%20the%20same.%20Recently%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-power-balance-employers-hiring-promotions-rto-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erocky%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20left%20many%20workers%20feeling%20like%20they%20can't%20change%20positions.%20And%20sometimes%20it's%20just%20easier%20to%20maintain%20the%20status%20quo.%20After%20all%2C%20change%20can%20be%20scary%20and%20comes%20with%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20workers%20who%20have%20experienced%20%26quot%3Bquiet%20cracking%26quot%3B%20told%20Business%20Insider%20why%20they%20felt%20trapped%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20they%20navigated%20their%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanel%20Douglas'%20initial%20reaction%20to%20reading%20about%20the%20%26quot%3Bquiet%20cracking%26quot%3B%20trend%20was%20simple%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%2C%20'Oh%20wow%2C%20it's%20not%20just%20me.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDouglas%20is%20a%20single%20mom%20in%20a%20small%20state%20and%20a%20niche%20position%20she%20worked%20her%20way%20to%20without%20a%20degree%2C%20which%20many%20jobs%20require.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20the%20life%20that%20I've%20built%20in%20this%20career%2C%20I%20feel%20very%20stuck%2C%20so%20I%20just%20go%20in%20every%20day%20and%20try%20really%20hard%20not%20to%20break%20by%20lunchtime%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%2037-year-old%20facility%20planner%20in%20healthcare%2C%20Douglas%20said%20she's%20more%20stressed%20at%20work%20than%20ever%20before%2C%20with%20multiple%20contributing%20factors%20coalescing%20to%20create%20what%20felt%20like%20%26quot%3Ba%20perfect%20storm.%26quot%3B%20Douglas%20said%20she%20consequently%20experienced%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20mental%20health%20challenges%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20a%20panic%20attack%20that%20led%20her%20to%20take%20a%20temporary%20leave%20to%20seek%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeeling%20trapped%20in%20a%20job%20isn't%20new%2C%C2%A0though%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bquiet%20cracking%26quot%3B%20is.%20Kevin%20Ford%2C%2056%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20experienced%20it%20over%2015%20years%20ago%20in%20an%20information%20technology%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFord%20felt%20misaligned%20with%20the%20company's%20management%20culture.%20He%20was%20learning%20about%20new%20areas%20of%20business%20in%20his%20MBA%20program%2C%20which%20he%20wanted%20to%20pursue.%20As%20a