o%20a%20full-time%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENoriega%20said%20his%20lifelong%20passion%20for%20entrepreneurship%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20a%20desire%20for%20a%20backup%20plan%20in%20case%20of%20a%20layoff%20%E2%80%94%20pulled%20him%20toward%20the%20third%20path.%20When%20he%20wasn't%20working%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20he%20dedicated%20time%20to%20a%20software%20education%20business%20that%20he'd%20begun%20developing%20before%20he%20moved%20to%20the%20US.%20After%20a%20few%20years%2C%20when%20the%20business%20didn't%20take%20off%20as%20he'd%20hoped%2C%20he%20shifted%20his%20focus%20to%20an%20online%20piano%20lessons%20venture%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20one%20also%20struggled%20to%20get%20off%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20he%20launched%20NTSprint%2C%20a%20staffing%20firm%20that%20helps%20Latin%20American%20software%20engineers%20access%20remote%20jobs%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada.%20Noriega%2C%20who%20is%20originally%20from%20Cuba%20and%20lived%20in%20Mexico%20for%20several%20years%2C%20said%20his%20goal%20was%20to%20help%20engineers%20in%20the%20region%20land%20higher-paying%20jobs%20and%20%26quot%3Bbreak%20the%20cycle%20of%20poverty%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Noriega%20has%20poured%20significant%20time%20and%20energy%20into%20building%20the%20business.%20In%20the%20year%20leading%20up%20to%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-layoffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20layoff%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20said%20his%20typical%20schedule%20involved%20finishing%20work%20at%205%20p.m.%2C%20then%20exercising%2C%20showering%2C%20and%20eating%20dinner%20before%20working%20on%20NTSprint%20from%208%20p.m.%20to%20midnight.%20In%20addition%20to%20those%20four-hour%20weeknights%2C%20he%20said%20he'd%20often%20spend%20up%20to%20eight%20hours%20on%20the%20business%20each%20Saturday%20and%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20working%20like%20crazy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENoriega%20said%20working%20on%20his%20business%20outside%20work%20hours%20was%20in%20compliance%20with%20Microsoft's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-microsoft-investor-march-1-2011-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoonlighting%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20he%20said%20allows%20employees%20to%20pursue%20side%20projects%20or%20businesses%20as%20long%20as%20it's%20done%20outside%20company%20hours%2C%20the%20business%20doesn't%20compete%20with%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20company%20resources%20aren't%20used.%20Noriega%20said%20he%20was%20transparent%20about%20his%20business%20with%20his%20manager%20and%20didn't%20face%20any%20pushback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229086b534-ed3b-41ca-9de8-1db53e2ef266%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWinning%20the%20'Microsoft%20game'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Microsoft%20laid%20him%20off%20in%20May%2C%20Noriega%20said%20he'd%20already%20been%20talking%20with%20his%20wife%20about%20whether%20he%20should%20quit%20his%20job%20and%20focus%20exclusively%20on%20his%20business.%20He%20said%20he%20was%20earning%20more%20money%20from%20the%20business%20than%20from%20his%20Microsoft%20role%2C%20and%20the%20long%20hours%20were%20taking%20a%20toll.%20However%2C%20he%20said%20he%20couldn't%20bring%20himself%20to%20resign%20%E2%80%94%20doing%20so%20would%20mean%20giving%20up%20a%20steady%20paycheck%2C%20excellent%20health%20insurance%2C%20and%20unvested%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENoriega%20said%20getting%20laid%20off%20by%20Microsoft%20was%20likely%20very%20difficult%20for%20most%20employees%2C%20but%20for%20him%2C%20it%20provided%20the%20push%20he%20needed%20to%20focus%20on%20his%20business%20full-time.%20He%20hasn't%20looked%20for%20another%20job%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20never%20dared%20to%20quit%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20Microsoft%20presented%20the%20layoff%2C%20and%20for%20me%2C%20that%20was%20like%20an%20exit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENoriega%20said%20he%20thinks%20people%20who%20have%20concerns%20about%20their%20job%20security%20should%20consider%20diversifying%20their%20incomes%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20through%20freelancing%2C%20consulting%2C%20or%20building%20a%20business.%20He%20knows%20this%20isn't%20feasible%20for%20everyone%2C%20but%20said%20doing%20so%20helped%20him%20blunt%20the%20financial%20and%20career%20impacts%20of%20his%20layoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20final%20days%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20Noriega%20said%20a%20coworker%20told%20him%20he%20%26quot%3Bwon%20the%20Microsoft%20game.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20she%20meant%20is%20that%20I%20worked%20hard%20for%20the%20company%2C%20but%20once%20I%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20I%20was%20not%20left%20empty-handed%20and%20in%20despair%2C%20rushing%20to%20get%20the%20next%20job%20to%20support%20my%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-microsoft-worker-side-business-job-security-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755245341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689e25f1194a2d49b8ae94ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-microsoft-worker-side-business-job-security-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Microsoft%20engineer%20of%2017%20years%20had%20long%20dreaded%20layoffs%20and%20sought%20job%20security.%20He%20chose%20to%20prioritize%20his%20side%20business%20over%20chasing%20promotions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzinkula%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20Zinkula)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-microsoft-worker-side-business-job-security-2025-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hurricane%20warning%3A%20Will%20Storm%20Erin%20trigger%20state%20of%20emergency%20in%20US%3F%20areas%20at%20risk%20and%20what%2